A Git Submodule is a Git repository inside another Git repository.
A submodule allows one Git project to include and use another Git project while keeping them as separate repositories.
Benefits:
•	No duplicate code 
•	Easy updates 
•	Independent version control 
•	Better code organization 
Add  a submodule
•	Syntax: git submodule add <repo-url>
•	Git creates a file name .gitmodules: it stores information about all submodules.
•	Clone a repo with submodules: git clone --recurse-submodules <repo-url>
•	Initialize existing subodules: git submodule init , then git submodule update or you can use git submodule update --init
•	Update a submodule: To fetch the latest chages from the submodule: 
git submodule update –remote
•	Check submodules: git submodule 
•	Remove a submodule: git submodule deinit submodule-name


